pallida
</emphasis>
(BALY, 1867) n. comb.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="376" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[867,1470,1469,2070]" pageId="3" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis box="[907,1129,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1860" box="[907,1045,1981,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiosterna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Plagiosterna</taxonomicName>
pallida
</emphasis>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1860" box="[1332,1470,1981,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiosterna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1332,1470,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="376">Plagiosterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1904" box="[876,972,2013,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenolina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[876,972,2013,2037]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="376">Xenolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<emphasis box="[991,1101,2014,2037]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="376">marginata</emphasis>
JACOBY, 1904 from New Guinea which might be considered as a junior synonym.
</paragraph>
